In article <j98fm2s@sgi.sgi.com> rpw3@rigden.wpd.sgi.com (Rob Warnock) writes:
>The "key" image *can* be pre-computed, and indeed can be
>used as the "key" for several coded images. [Hey, this is neat!]

Using the same key twice has the same problem as using a one-time pad
twice.  In fact, I suspect (though I don't have any here to try with)
that if you used two encoded images from the same key as a pair, you'd
see something much like the two plain-images superimposed.

